      <h2 id="spreadsheet-liability"><i class="fas fa-calculator mr-3 text-[#489DF9]"></i>The Spreadsheet Ceiling: Why Manual Estimation is a Liability</h2>
      <p>
        For decades, the spreadsheet was the gold standard for construction estimating. It offered flexibility, low cost, and a familiar interface. However, in the high-stakes environment of 2025, that flexibility has become a "key-man risk." When your entire bidding process lives in a complex web of Excel macros and hidden formulas known only to one senior estimator, you are one corrupted file or one retirement away from a total operations breakdown.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beyond the risk of data loss, spreadsheets create a scalability bottleneck. Manual data entry is slow, prone to transposition errors, and disconnected from real-time market data. In a market characterized by <strong>Supply Chain Volatility</strong>, relying on static <strong>Unit Rates</strong> updated once a quarter is a recipe for underbidding.
      </p>

